Azure Public IP - Quick Notes
What is a Public IP?

A Public IP Address in Azure allows Azure resources (VMs, Load Balancers, Application Gateways, etc.) to communicate with the Internet.

Common Use Cases
Access a Virtual Machine from the Internet (SSH/RDP)
Expose a web application
Associate with a Load Balancer
Associate with an Application Gateway
Ingress traffic for AKS
Create a Public IP
Command
az network public-ip create \
  --resource-group <resource-group-name> \
  --name <public-ip-name>
Example
az network public-ip create \
  --resource-group kml_rg_main-616ff0398a0e415d \
  --name devops-pip
Verify Public IP
List all Public IPs
az network public-ip list \
  --resource-group kml_rg_main-616ff0398a0e415d \
  -o table
Show details of a specific Public IP
az network public-ip show \
  --resource-group kml_rg_main-616ff0398a0e415d \
  --name devops-pip
Important Properties
Property	Description
Name	Name of the Public IP
Resource Group	Container holding Azure resources
IP Address	Actual public IP assigned
Allocation Method	Static or Dynamic
SKU	Basic or Standard
Location	Azure Region
Provisioning State	Succeeded/Failed
Static vs Dynamic IP
Static	Dynamic
Never changes	Can change
Preferred for production	Mostly used for testing
Fixed endpoint	Temporary endpoint

Example:

Static IP: 20.127.34.8
